{
  "texts": [
    "For QA engineers, testers, and development managers, the adoption of AI signifies more than a tool upgrade-it represents a shift in roles, responsibilities, and required competencies.",
    "Traditional testing skillsets centered around scripting and manual analysis must now be complemented with knowledge of AI principles, data science, and machine learning workflows.",
    "Organizations must invest in upskilling QA teams, redesigning test strategies, and reconfiguring toolchains to fully capitalize on AI's potential.",
    "Furthermore, test automation strategies must evolve to become AI-first, where systems not only execute tests but also learn from previous cycles, adapt test coverage in real time, and generate insights that feed directly into development and release planning.",
    "Despite its potential, the integration of AI into QA is not without limitations."
  ]
}